                            <comment id="98466" author="paf" created="Wed, 5 Nov 2014 20:29:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/12524/2&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/12524/2&lt;/a&gt; breaks mounts of MGS/MGT volumes with short names (which is valid for an MGS/MDT, since they do not have to include an index or the file system name).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;root@centss02 ~&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;# mount -t lustre -o abort_recov /dev/sdb /tmp/lustre/centss02/mgt&lt;br/&gt;
mount.lustre: invalid name &apos;MGS&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Since the entire purpose of that code is to fix up OST &amp;amp; MDT names to indicate their status, presumably the solution is to simply not call this check on the MGS/MGT volume.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll open a new LU for this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
